Game 07

Overview

Real World Date: 01/11/2020

Game Date: 10/05/2020 - ~3:00p

TLDR

YouTube: https://youtu.be/kuTrZ3F-RjI?t=8052

Summary: • Trent is discovering that he is in a dream. But it isn’t his dream it is Kira’s

• After failing to try and wake her up he helps her fight back.

• Xen returns Dyron to Vic and Vic Reaches out to his Uncle Owen

• During the return, Duces 8 shows up and there was a fire fight.

• Dyron, got shot in the head and died. Then… he didn’t.

Game Notes

“As I walk, as I walk; The universe is walking with me; In beauty it walks before me; In beauty it walks behind me; In beauty it walks below me; In beauty it walks above me; Beauty is on every side; As I walk, I walk with Beauty.” Sani thinks to himself repeating the words he has heard many times. He opens his eyes finishing his morning meditation. Looking out to the city from Victor Steinbrueck Park. His phone rings and on checking his caller ID, he sees it is from Trent. “Hello?”

“Do you know someone one by the name of Travis? He has long green and blue… maybe… hair?” a panicked Kasey , the girl from the dorm that lost her roommate Ella , asks.

Sani told her he did not and tried to get her off the phone. She started listing names she sees on his phone. “These are his recent contacts. Please, help.”

“I think you may mean Trent .” Sani tells her. “What is going on?”

She tells him what has happened, and he agrees to come down. “Well. Should have known today was not going to get any easier.” Sani stands up and makes his way towards Seattle University.

Trent is standing on the shoreline of the docks. He has never seen this place before. But it feels like it should be familiar. The sand on the shoreline doesn’t quite feel right. It isn’t sticking to his shoes. But the air smells right. There are other little things that seem off, but Trent can’t quite put his finger on it.

At the end of the docks there is a girl, with her back turned, in a white night gown. She turns around and Trent can see stab marks in her stomach “Oh that may be what is off”, he thinks. She drops a pair of scissors and looks at someone approaching.

It is her sister. How does Trent know that? He is not sure, but he does. “Kira! No! Wait!” she screams, but just like a dream objects appear close, but take so long to get to.

“Goodbye Ella ” Kira whispers as she falls into the water. Kira dives after her.

“FUCK!” Trent says out loud to no one. He quickly starts making his way down the dock all thoughts that something is off forgotten. Trent looks down at the water and can see the two girls sinking deeper and deeper.

Trent reaches out with his mind. Everything seems off here. He can sense… Kasey ? She was (... is?) Kira’s dormmate. Looking around he doesn’t see her, but she is close. He pushes that away for now and pulls up his memory of everything in his shadow room. “Rope.” He thinks and says out loud to himself. He reaches through a shadow under the dock and grabs his rope.

Kasey is standing in the dorm room holding Trent ’s cellphone and hangs up with a confused Sani . “What the fuck is going on?” she says, thinking she may be losing her mind. All a sudden a rope drops from nowhere, I mean literally nowhere, right onto the floor in front of her. She screams as a hand reaches from under the bed and grabs the rope and pulls it under.

Kasey stumbles back to the wall and slowly slides down until she is sitting staring at what just happened, not blinking.

Trent has the rope tied to him and the dock and he dives into the water. “Something didn’t feel right” he thinks. He has felt splashing into water before, and it felt close, but not… right. “Is this a dream?” he thinks.

“STOP!” Trent pushes the thought from his mind into theirs. They stop sinking and turn to look up at him. Ella turns to look back at Kira, but at some point, she disappeared into the darkness. Ella starts to enter the surprise stage of drowning. She tilts to the vertical position and tries to climb up, but not moving in a motion that is best for swimming.

“Relax. This isn’t real.” Trent pushes another thought into Kira. She slows her moving, and reaches out and grabs the water, and pulls it over her like they are blankets.

Trent stands up form kneeling. He is dry and in a bedroom. There are two beds and stuff laying all around. It feels like a teenager or younger’s bedroom. The walls are bright pink and there is a nightlight that shines blue in the corner.

Trent tries to read her mind, but he is getting images and feedback that he can’t make sense of. None of his magickal perceptions are making any sense. This place feels real, but it also doesn’t at the same time.

“What are you doing here?” Kira asks.

“My name is Trent . A mutual friend was worried and asked if I could check on you. Could you tell me where we are?”

Kira stops looking at Trent and off in the distance, “A nightmare.”

“None of this look familiar?” Trent asks.

Kira rolls her eyes, “It all looks familiar. This is my childhood bedroom.”

Trent a little confused, “Then what makes this a nightmare?”

“Just wait” Kira goes back to staring at nothing “You will see.”

 

Trent follows her stare and is looking at a dresser with a mirror on it. “I don’t…” he begins, but his gut dropped.

Before him stands (… hovers? Floats? What is the correct word for what ghost do?) Kira. She slowly starts to float toward Ella on the bed.

Trent stands between them “Why are you here, what do you want?”.

The spirit reaches out with her arm and says “Move” as she tries to push Trent away. Trent duck and moved so he didn’t go flying across the room.

But that thing is strong, and he thought to himself "apparently if she can touch me, I can touch her". Trent reaches into his jacket and into his shadow room.

Sani comes walking down the dorm hall surprised to see so many kids standing around in the hall. There are maybe 20 plus students in the hall, holding candles, crying, praying, laying tokens of appreciation, and more. “Hey,” Sani taps someone on the shoulder, “What happened here?”

“We are here for the girl that disappeared.” The student replied. Sani pushed for more. “A girl was taken. She went to her room and vanished. We are here for her.”

“Really?”, Sani addresses the hall. “You believe this crap? You all are at a place of higher learning and this is the best explanation you got? What do they teach you in physics? Is the world still round?”

A student starts to speak up “Well actually, there are…”

“Shut up!” Sani , doesn’t have time for this crap. “This is obviously a trick and you all are eating it up.” Sani goes on to answer some of their random ‘but what about…’ questions.

“The guy, that came to visit, he was taken too.” One speaks up.

“He called me.” Sani pulls out his flip phone, looks at the screen, put on his readers, leans over to another in the hall to have her show him how to accesses recent contacts, and points. “Not even an hour ago to come get him. Stop this. You are smarter than this, or is what they say about Seattle U true?”

One of the students says, “I told you this was a Hoax.” He grabs his stuff and starts to leave, and others follow.

Some stay so Sani presses on. “Did you know this person? Their mother, father, hopes, and dreams?”

“ Ella was the child of Margret and Tom, she lived on 335 Ellington road. Her favorite hobby is playing Pixie and Black Dog game. I bought her the players guide to use. She uses a lavender in her laundry. She always wears different color socks. She hopes one day we will end up together.” He says

Sani just got creeper vibes. “Get the fuck out of here you little stalker.” He steps up to the kid.

The Student tries to stand but trips, and then takes off. “OK, Boomer!” he yells back at Sani .

“What a weird name to give a kid. Boomer?” He thinks to himself as he knocks on the door.

Kasey opens the door. “Are you Trent ’s grandfather?” In the bedroom they both hear a thud and tumble. They look back there and see nothing.

Trent reached into his jacket and into his shadow room. He grabs his mallet and pulls, it falls onto the bedroom floor and as he reached for it again it slipped into another shadow and fell back into the shadow room knocking over his stash of weed. Trent pulls his arm out of his jacket holding nothing and said, “What the hell.” He grabbed a chair and hit her but didn’t get the effect he hoped for.

It went right through her. He stumbles to the other side. When he turns around Kira is sitting on top of Ella poking at her stomach.

“BACK OFF!” Trent blast at Kira. Both Ella and Kira scream, and Kira starts ripping at her stomach and pulls her insides out, entrails piling on top of Ella . This make Trent a little sick to this stomach.

“Ummm, yeah, I am his grandfather.” Sani replies. “He get’s his hair from me.” Kasey takes Sani to the room and walks him through everything that has happened. He can tell she is freaking out and maybe even thinks she is going crazy.

“When is the last time you have gotten sleep?” Sani says to Kasey . “I hear what you are saying and I believe you, but I also know you are under a lot of stress from school, those kids outside, your roommate… who I think may also have been a friend… disappeared. You need a break and maybe things to return to normal.”

“I know what I saw!” she rebutted.

Sani nodding. “I know, and again I believe you. Let’s get some tea, and try and approach this from another angle.”

Trent blinks and the room is dark except for a dim lamp that is on one of their nightstands. The two girls are on the other bed giggling and talking about something. Trent is still trying to shake what he just saw to pay too much attention. A loud BANG comes from the door.

There stands a man, wearing a blue baseball cap and glasses, standing at the door with a tray of two warm cups of milk. “Sorry. Stupid door.” He comes on in “It is time for bed.” He sits the cups down on the bed and goes over to close the window. They grab the cups and start to sip. The father sits with them and chats, then tucks them in for sleep.

The room is only lit by moonlight now. Trent is watching this play out. He see’s Ella put her finger to her lips in a shhhh symbol. The door creaks open. And two long tentacle like arms reach in and come crawling their way into the room. The monster slowly creeps up to the bed and hovers over Kira. He head shifts and pulls out of the creature’s shell and it is wearing that blue hat and the glasses are reflective of the moon’s light. A long tongue comes out and starts to lick the face of Kira.

Trent makes his way over to Ella , “What did your father do?”

“I THOUGHT I TOLD YOU TO *GO* *TO* *SLEEP* !” the father monster yelled out.

“You are not supposed to let it know you’re awake.” Ella said as she started to roll over as a long tentacle arm comes down and smacks the bed.

Trent tries to put Ella into a deeper sleep to try and stop the nightmare. He gets pushed back by her will. “Son of a Bitch that bounce back hurts.” Then jumps out of the way as the tentacle arm slaps the shit out of Trent . “Nope…" he says through a grunt, "that hurts more.”

Trent then feels Sani walk into the room and close a door, but he can’t see him here. “Help!” he sends to Sani using his Mind.

“I hear you, but I don’t see you.” Sani replies.

“How the fuck do I get him here?” Trent thinks to himself.

Puck speaks up “Hey fucker, I have an idea.”

“I’m Listening.” He yells back as another arm comes crashing down and he rolls out of the way.

“Teleport the old man’s mind into the kids body.” Puck suggest.

“I can’t do that.”

“Why would I waste your time… Move!” Trent jumps and rolls out of the way “…and mine suggesting something that you couldn’t do.”

“Listen fucker, I can’t teleport people. I could kill them if they let me try.”

“I never suggested to teleport him. I said teleport his mind.”

“I can do that?” Trent asks

“I don’t know, but it is going to be a blast watching you try.” Puck replies.

“I hate you.”

“I know.”

Trent reaches out with his mind and flies into the dorm room. “Oh, this is how Ella did it.” He reaches for Sani and Sani instinctively throws up a wall of will. Trent slams into that wall, “Mother Fucker!” Trent yells as he slams back into the room.

“Sweet.” Puck chuckles.

Sani uses his Life to sense what is happening in the room and can feel two people. His sense grab on to Trent and Trent grabs back and pulls. They go flying from the dorm and into a bedroom Sani getting slammed into the sleeping Kira and Trent slamming back into the floor. “For a dream, I am going to feel this when I wake up.” Trent grunts to himself.

On a day like today, one wouldn’t recognize Vic . He is standing in, what he would call, full tactical gear. He is angry. The street light beside him is flickering and his hand is glowing with fire. He glances up at the sign above the building “ 8 is Enough ”. Vic is ready to burn it all down. Dee has been getting worse. Talking to himself. Getting mood swings. This must be what it is like to become a ghost or maybe he was always like this. Vic ’s phone rings. “I don’t have time for this right now.” He says to himself, and glances at the caller ID. It is Xenori .

Xen is standing on a street corner with Dyron . She is holding her phone up and after the 3 rd ring almost gives up to text when she hears Vic answer. “You still looking for Dyron ?” She asks.

“Yep, just about to pick him up.”

“You’re what?” Xen seems confused. “I got him.”

Vic rolls his eyes. ‘Great, she is in the bar, so burning it to the ground is not an option.’ He thinks to himself. “What are you doing in the bar?”

“I’m… not, but a beer sounds great right about now.” She replies. “We are in the Queen Anne District. I think I see a Starbucks up the road, I can text you my location.” Her bike pulls around the corner and Dyron is shocked no one is driving it. She walks over towards it and nods to Dyron to get on.

Vic gets a text as she is telling him this. He glances, “Well that would have been awkward.” Vic mumbles. “Yeah, I’ll be there, I am in Central District right now.”

Vic extinguishes his flame and gets in his car and leaves. At the bar window a guy turns around “He left.”

Tyrone is flipping a card between his fingers and pulling a slight of hand to make it vanish and reappear, “That means he found him.” He takes a look at the business card “Victor Black, I am eventually going to have to put you on the payroll if you keep doing me favors.”

Xenori and Dyron at Starbucks waiting on Vic . Dyron asks “How did they find you?”

“The Spiders?” Xen asks. Seeing Dyron nod she tells him about how she was investigating the attacks on the homeless and followed a guy into a building where they jumped her. She shivered remembering the number of spiders that crawled across her.

Dyron remembers what it was like for him as well and he shakes almost dropping his coffee.

“It’s cool now.” Xen says, “We got you.” Right about then Vic comes walking in. He is wearing most of his tactical gear still except for his mask. Some people look a little nervous. When the door closes the lights flicker and one of the milk steamers kick on to the employees surprise.

‘Need to chill Vic , you don’t need to burn down a coffee shop.’ He thinks to himself.

“Holy Shit!” Dee says to him, “You actually did it.” He goes running up to Dyron taking a look at him knowing that he can’t see him back.

“ Dyron .” Vic calls when he gets up to the table. Dyron doesn’t know him and looks at him cautiously. “I have been looking all over for you. I know your brother.”

“You knew my brother.” Dyron replied.

“Trust me.” Vic mumbles “I wish.”

“Fuck you.” Dee says to Vic as Vic smirks back at him.

“What did he owe you.” Dyron said.

“Ouch.” Dee says. “I really fucked him up.”

“Actually.” Vic says, “It is more like I owe him. I have been trying to find you before Tyrone could and get you to your uncle.”

“That would be nice.” Dyson admits, “But, He wouldn’t take me.”

“He is on his way. He is actually pretty excited to see you again.” Vic says.

 “How do I know I can trust you?”

Dee nudges Vic , “Tell him to get the basket.”

Vic “Go get the basket.”

Dyron tears up “Holy Shit.”

“Hey now!” Dee says like he has replied this 100 times with Dyron and his language.

“I mean… Let’s do this!” Dyron replies. Vic knows that Dyron couldn't hear Dee, but this must have been routine becasue they both "interacted" with one another. Vic can feel this is what magick is really about, humanity and what little still exist is important to save.

Vic hands him a few bucks to go pay for the drinks and watches Dyron run off. “The Basket?”

“Down in Central, they don’t keep the hoops netted. So we had to bring our own. I would always tell him to grab the basket. It was our thing. As we got older that was our way of communicating ‘This is serious’, and we never abused it.” Dee told him.

“The what?” Xen replies.

“Nothing.” Vic shrugs it off. “How did you find him?”

“Let’s say I was in the web, and not the good kind.” Xen says a little freaked out.

Dyron comes back “We were kidnapped by spiders.”

Vic looks confused and Xenori chimes in, “I wish he was lying.”

“Spiders?” Vic asks and thinks a little bit. He doesn’t remember anything on spider monsters.

“Lots of spiders.” Xen continues, “Lots and Lots of spiders.”

“It got real B movie up in there.” Dyron said.

“Did you kill them with fire?” Vic asks.

“We just barely got away.” Xen said. “They nabbed me at West Bridge, and when I woke up they had us tangled in some webs at Gas Works Park .”

Vic remembers seeing her down at Westbridge when he was looking for Dyron . “Well, you ready?” Vic ask, tabling that conversation for now.

“You coming with us?” Dyron asked Xenori

“Sure kid.” Xen replied.

Vic calls Owen on the way to his car. Owen let’s Vic know that he can meet them at the International Fountain in about two hours. Vic takes his car and Xen rides with Dyron on the back of her bike.

Kira… well Sani , but posing as Kira… stands up on the bed, looks around the room, and says “What the fuck?”

The Monster turns his head “ Language little one .” Then proceeds to slap Kira ( Sani ) across the face.

Kira gets knocked across the room, but somewhere else Sani is standing in the dorm room and stumbles backward and bumps he head against the wall. His consciousness comes back to Kira. Kira struggles to stand up and looks across the room at her sister, “ Ella ! You need to fight. You need to save us. You can end this. Fight him!”

Ella stands up and looks at the monster. Trent hands her a Zippo Lighter. This is something real. When she wraps her hands around it, it isn’t like anything she has touched in here. She uses it to ground her and turns to the monster dad. “Fuck you!”

The monster turns to her “You are going to get it.”

“No!” She jumps at the creature and so does Trent and Kira. Trent and Kira hold the creature and try to prevent the tentacle arms swinging while Ella lands on him and starts punching. “I HATE YOU! I HATE YOU!” she says over and over as she weeps and attacks.

Sani grabs his rattle snake fang and crushes it into the monster pushing an Entropy effect that starts to age the creature. The creature quickly and rapidly started to decline. Ella could see the breathing tubes in his nose. The monster looked scared and ashamed, but she didn’t care.

Ella took the lighter and jabbed it into his eye. It burst and she kept pounding over and over until the monster was dust. She landed on the soft ground on her knees dropping the lighter. She pulled her hands to her face and sobbed. Trent came running over to her, picked up the lighter, then reached out to hold her and let her know it was going to be ok.

She allowed it for a moment, but then tapped out. She had to push him away a little, and Trent got the hint and backed off. He sat beside her on the grass. They were no longer in the bedroom. The world had changed around them and they were now at a cemetery. They were sitting on the bright green grass looking out among beautiful field. “I couldn’t do anything…”

“That’s ok.” Trent reassured her.

“I know.” She said, “I meant, I physically couldn’t do anything. He put sleep medicine in the milk. He would put a little less for her and I grabbed his cup by accident. It kept me awake enough to see, but weak enough to not act.”

They sat there a while. “Why am I in hell?”

“You’re not.” Trent said “I think we are in a dream.”

“Actually,” Sani interrupts. He is back in the dorm and has had a moment to observe the scene with his Prime vision, “You two are caught up in a Paradox Backlash, kind of a bad one.”

Trent can hear Sani in his head. He asks Ella , “So what happens next?”

“It starts over.” Ella says.

“The docks?” Trent asks.

“No.” Ella answers, “There are more moments that I experience before I get to the docks.”

“What were you doing before all this?” Trent asks.

“That was so long ago.” She thought out loud. “I was in my dorm. I have this trick I do, actually I am not sure how I do it, but I can flick the TV on and change the channels. It freaks my roommate out. I wonder how Kasey is doing.”

“I think you can do magick.” Trent tells her. She of course laughs because that is a very absurd thing to say, but Trent waits for her to realize it is not.

“I know you find it weird.” Trent says in her head, “But it is real.” He creates an illusion of snow the falling flakes are actually little snow figures of him and Ella .

“and… I can do that?” Ella asks

“Maybe.” Trent replies, “We all have different talents or tricks. But you can do something and I think that is what got you here.” They stand up and Trent looks for a tree to grab a shadow from. “Can I help you travel? I don’t know where I am at, so I am going to need you to navigate.” Ella consents and grabs his arms. “Picture the remote.”

They pop and sore through the unknown. Ella reaches out and can see the remote. She grabs it and says “ahh, yeah. Here it is.” She pulls and Trent gets dragged along with her. They burst out into the living room where Kasey is watching TV, curled up on the couch, and drinking some hot tea. Obviously, she screams and spills her drink everywhere.

She gets up and runs over to Ella and hugs her. “I don’t understand.”

Trent , Sani , and Ella look at one another with the realization that explaining is damned near impossible. But they are all relieved to have saved Ella and now she is home.

Sani ’s pocket starts to ring. He pulls out the phone and tosses it over to Trent . It is Sasha trying to call. “Hello?” Trent answers on speaker.

“I can’t explain why, but you need to get to the Space Needle now!” and hangs up. Everyone stares at the phone wishing there was more explanation, but none was forth coming.

“You can get there faster than I can.” Sani says.

Trent tells Sani , “Catchup as fast as you can.” He looks over at Ella , “Sorry, I got to help, but while I am gone don’t try anymore tricks. I can try and help you figure this all out.” He takes her phone and calls himself. “I gotta go.” Trent walks over to the door and opens it to create a darker shadow on the wall and jumps in.

“Am I losing my mind?” Kasey asks the room. Sani and Ella start laughing.

“We all are.” Sani says. He takes a quick moment to tell Ella to come up with a good story. There were a lot of people who were paying attention to her disappearance. He walks out and there was a bus pulling up.

“Hey buddy there was an accident so I have to skip most of my route. My next stop is the Space Needle.” The driver says.

Sani gives a knowing smile and tells the driver, “That will be fine.” and proceeds to climb onto the bus.

Trent opens a door from a service station and come stumbling out to Downtown District underneath the Space Needle. Trent ’s thoughts are still back with Ella , “Puck, did we go to some dream world?”

“When your kind dreams worlds are created, but you don’t know enough to get there.” Puck replies. “I believe she simply teleported herself into her subconscious.” 

“What you’re saying is impossible.” Trent responds logically, “If someone tried to teleport to where they were, they wouldn’t be there anymore so they would have nowhere to go. It is similar to the time travel paradox.”

“Exactly.”

“What?”

“You’re finally asking the right question.” Puck comments.

Trent hears gun shots off in the distance and does what everyone else isn’t. He runs towards the sound.

Vic , Xenori , Dyron , and Uncle Owen meet that the bottom of the fountain. When Owen first sees Dyron he is thrilled and runs up to hug him “Damn you have grown.”

“I really thought you wanted nothing to do with me after last time.” Dyron said.

Owen looks at him very seriously. “I have been a father 7 times over. You don’t come close to the worst things that have been said to me by loved ones. We all say stupid shit, but what is important is what is in here.” He says pointing to the boys heart.

Xen hears something in the distance, but Vic is not recognizing it at the moment. She looks around and notices a few cars approaching. They are driving off road heading straight to the fountain. “Ummm. Vic ?” But they were already stopping and jumping out of their cars. “Friends of yours?”

“I didn’t do anything.” Vic responds and looks over at Xen giving him the raised eyebrow. “This time!”

“The boy is coming with me.” Tyrone yells from across the fountain. At this time most the people have scattered and ran from the scene. Tyrone and Duces 8 are standing around the fountain with their weapons drawn. “He is staying with family.”

“He is with family.” Xenori comments.

“ Tyrone !” Owen yells “I have appreciated all you have done. You where there when the boy’s mother died, and you were there when his brother died. But he needs a real home now. I can provide him that. This boy has too much potential to live this life.”

“Cute.” Tyrone responds. “He owes me too much. He owes me blood.”

“How much is that worth to you?” Vic says. (I swear, I think Vic has found the lost 10 th sphere, money)

“Is the boy some kind of Charity Case for you?” Tyrone questions.

“I owe his brother, that is all.” Vic respond to the slight.

Tyrone smirks at that answer, “Nagh, I know you. You are the guy that did the job for me.”

“I don’t know what you’re talking about.” Vic taking control of the conversation, “You don’t want to do this the hard way. Walk away, let the boy go. We can talk about compensation, but end this!”

“Bitch!” Tyrone looks around, “There are 25 of us. You don’t have authority here. I think this is a pretty easy choice for you all. Just stand down, you won’t get hurt. Look I owe you. My brother was getting in the way. You took care of that, Victor Black.” He says while slight of hands a business card from his sleeve.

“Listen Tyrone .” Vic didn’t like that someone having access to his card, that he didn’t personally hand out. “There are things you do not understand. Things that are above your comprehension.”

“Yeah, I saw what you did to Stubs over there.” Tyrone snips back.

“Wow! Quick with the nicknames.” Xen snips while wondering when these two were going to stop their pissing contest. But also kind of hoping it doesn’t end without a plan to get out of here.

“Give me the boy.” Tyrone lifts his gun and aims it at Owen, “I can make this very easy for you.”

Vic mumbles a couple words under his breath, and tuts his fingers in the correct jester and waits for the gun to explode once the trigger is pulled.

“Oh, ok.” Xen says, “We are escalading. Ketunnahka may need your help.”

The gun goes off, but it doesn’t explode. Vic feels a sense of hollowness. A spell he has worked a thousand times ( ST Note: I am now imagining a support group for people that pulled a gun on Vic ) and this was the first time he didn’t feel connected to the energies. The bullet races down towards Owen. Xen running over to push him out of the way, but at the last second Dyron stepped in front of his Uncle.

Everyone screams, swears, or curses. Dyron head jerks back and everyone sees blood splatter out the other side. He falls back and hits the pavement. More gunfire explodes and Xen realizes she isn’t going to make it to Owen in time. She uses her Correspondence and Forces to send her BUGs to push Owen down. Ketunnahka, roars around to block them from one side, but they are in a kill hole.

Vic pulls the trigger and focuses his Forces to give the bullet an extra punch. It hits Tyrone right in the chest. He flies back and hits the ground. Trent arrives and takes a big puff. When he blows it out a lot of smoke comes out like if someone blasted open a smoke machine. Vic and Xenori start running across the fountain. The gunmen start following their path.

Vic comes charging through the smoke. The gunmen confused as they just saw him run up the fountain. Vic slides low as they turn back and he start releasing a fury of bullets. After running out, he quickly reloads and sends a new array of bullets the other direction. In a matter of seconds Vic took down about 10 men. Vic notices that the fountain water starts to freeze in midair. He continues running up to Xen and Owen and ducked with them behind her bike.

Vic prepping his next attack when they all hear something move next to them. Dyron sits up and grabs his head. “Shit. I think I am bleeding.” The gun fire starts to die down and they notice everyone is starting to run. In the distance they can also hear police sirens.

Vic walks up to where he suspected Tyrone fell, but he was gone. He notices some blood on the ground and pulls out a cloth to dab it up.

At about the same time Sani come stepping off a bus and walks out into the park. He sees the aftermath of a gang fight and starts pulsing through his mage sight. Sani notices something weird on the ground. He goes over and notices he can see it, but it not with any of his mage visions. He reaches down to pick it up and it snapped. There was a loud pop, the fountain unfroze, and the bullet bunt him. He drops it and can feel the cyote inside him rage.  After he composes himself he rips off a piece of cloth, and ties up the bullet.

The police sirens are getting louder. Everyone take a quick look over Dyron using their mage site. They can’t find any magick, but Sani notices he is healing a quick rate. They decide to get out of there and regroup. Vic and Sani jump in his car, Xenori and Trent jump on her bike, and Owen and Dyron jump in Owen’s minivan.
